sentence.text: The aetiology of L-phenylalanine catabolic process is heterogeneous, and genetics play an important role in some cases.

Group 1 pulmonary hypertension or pulmonary arterial hypertension (L-phenylalanine catabolic process) is a rare disease characterized by proliferation and occlusion of small pulmonary arterioles, leading to progressive elevation of pulmonary artery pressure and pulmonary vascular resistance, and right ventricular failure.
